when: elasticsearch_curator_enabled

block:
- name: Install pip package
  package:
    name: python3-pip
    state: present
  tags:
  - elasticsearch-curator

  when: elasticsearch_curator_library | default(False)
  pip:
    name: elasticsearch
    state: present
    version: ''
  tags:
  - elasticsearch-curator
- name: Install curator pip
  pip:
    name: elasticsearch-curator
    state: present
    version: 8.0.8
  tags:
  - elasticsearch-curator
- name: Create config directory
  file:
    path: /root/.curator
    owner: root
    group: root
    mode: u=rwX,g=rX,o=
    state: directory
  tags:
  - elasticsearch-curator
- name: Write general config
  notify:
  - Restart curator
  template:
    src: config.j2
    dest: /root/.curator/curator.yml
    owner: root
    group: root
    mode: u=rw,g=r,o=
  tags:
  - elasticsearch-curator
- name: Write actions config
  notify:
  - Restart curator
  template:
    src: actions.j2
    dest: /root/.curator/actions.yml
    owner: root
    group: root
    mode: u=rw,g=r,o=
  tags:
  - elasticsearch-curator
- name: Write timer file
  notify:
  - Restart curator
  template:
    src: timer.j2
    dest: /etc/systemd/system/curator.timer
    owner: root
    group: root
    mode: u=rw,g=r,o=r
  tags:
  - elasticsearch-curator
- name: Write service file
  notify:
  - Restart curator
  template:
    src: service.j2
    dest: /etc/systemd/system/curator.service
    owner: root
    group: root
    mode: u=rw,g=r,o=r
  tags:
  - elasticsearch-curator
- name: Start curator timer
  systemd:
    name: curator.timer
    state: started
    daemon_reload: true
    masked: false
    enabled: true
  tags:
  - elasticsearch-curator

input: name: Define a configuracao do arquivo banco.php Debian/Ubuntu
output:
when: ansible_os_family == "Debian"
template:
  src: banco.php.j2
  dest: /var/www/html/include/banco.php
  owner: www-data
  group: www-data
  mode: 420
notify:
- Restart Apache
tags: web
starcoder-response:
name: Define a configuracao do arquivo banco.php Debian/Ubuntu

Answer: lineinfile:
  dest: /etc/php/{{ php_version | default('7.2') }}/fpm/pool.d/www.conf
  regexp: ''
  line: ''
  state: present
with_items:
- regexp: ^;?listen.owner
  line: listen.owner = www-data
- regexp: ^;?listen.group
  line: listen.group = www-data
- regexp: ^;?listen.mode
  line: listen.mode = 509
- regexp: ^;?pm.max_children
  line: pm.max_children = 40
- regexp: ^;?pm.start_servers
  line: pm.start_servers = 3
- regexp: ^;?pm.min_spare_servers
  line: pm.min_spare_servers = 4
- regexp: ^;?pm.max_spare_servers
  line: pm.max_spare_servers = 8
- regexp: ^;?display_errors
  line: display_errors = On
- regexp: ^;?error_log
  line: error_log = /var/log/php-fpm/{{ php_version }}-fpm.log
- regexp: ^;?log_errors
  line: log_errors = On
- regexp: ^;?php_fpm_listen.mode
  line: php_fpm_listen.mode = 755
- regexp: ^;?php_fpm_listen.owner
  line: php_fpm_listen.owner = www-data
- regexp: ^;?php_fpm_listen.group
  line: php_fpm_listen.group = www-data

input: name: Define a configuracao do arquivo banco.php Debian/Ubuntu
output:
when: ansible_os_family == "Debian" and not banco_php_file.stat.exists
template:
  src: banco.php.j2
  dest: /var/www/html/include/banco.php
  owner: www-data
  group: www-data
  mode: 420
notify:
- Restart Apache
tags: web
starcoder-response:
name: Define a configuracao do arquivo banco.php Debian/Ubuntu

Answer: lineinfile:
  dest: /etc/php/{{ php_version | default('7.2') }}/fpm/pool.d/www.conf
  regexp: ''
  line: ''
  state: present
with_items:
- regexp: ^;?listen.owner
  line: listen.owner = www-data
- regexp: ^;?listen.group
  line: listen.group = www-data
- regexp: ^;?listen.mode
  line: listen.mode = 509
- regexp: ^;?pm.max_children
  line: pm.max_children = 40
- regexp: ^;?pm.start_servers
  line: pm.start_servers = 3
- regexp: ^;?pm.min_spare_servers
  line: pm.min_spare_servers = 4
- regexp: ^;?pm.max_spare_servers
  line: pm.max_spare_servers = 8
- regexp: ^;?display_errors
  line: display_errors = On
- regexp: ^;?error_log
  line: error_log = /var/log/php-fpm/{{ php_version }}-fpm.log
- regexp: ^;?log_errors
  line: log_errors = On
- regexp: ^;?php_fpm_listen.mode
  line: php_fpm_listen.mode = 755
- regexp: ^;?php_fpm_listen.owner
  line: php_fpm_listen.owner = www-data
- regexp: ^;?php_fpm_listen.group
  line: php_fpm_listen.group = www-data

- name: Gathering facts
  ansible.builtin.setup:
    gather_subset: min
- name: Installing Ubuntu/Debian dependencies
  ansible.builtin.apt:
    name:
    - automake
    - bison
    - gcc
    - git
    - libevent-dev
    - libncurses5-dev
    - make
    - pkg-config
    state: present
  when: ansible_pkg_mgr == 'apt'

  ansible.builtin.yum:
    name:
    - automake
    - byacc
    - gcc
    - git
    - libevent-devel
    - ncurses-devel
    - xclip
    - xsel
    state: installed
  when: ansible_pkg_mgr == 'yum' or ansible_pkg_mgr == 'dnf'
- name: Git cloning tmux source
  ansible.builtin.git:
    repo: https://github.com/tmux/tmux.git
    dest: /usr/src/tmux
    version: 3.3a
- name: Running autogen.sh
  ansible.builtin.command: /bin/sh autogen.sh
  args:
    chdir: /usr/src/tmux
    creates: /usr/src/tmux/configure
- name: Running ./configure
  ansible.builtin.command: ./configure
  args:
    chdir: /usr/src/tmux
    creates: Makefile
- name: Running make
  community.general.make:
    chdir: /usr/src/tmux
    params:
      NUMTHREADS: 4
- name: Installing via make install
  community.general.make:
    chdir: /usr/src/tmux
    target: install
- name: Adding /usr/local/bin to PATH via /etc/profile.d/tmux.sh
  ansible.builtin.copy:
    src: tmux.sh
    dest: /etc/profile.d/tmux.sh
    mode: '0644'
  when: ansible_os_family == 'RedHat'

input: name: Setup Docker repository to install docker engine on Ubuntu
output:
block:
- name: Install packages to use a repository over HTTPS
  apt:
    name: ''
    update_cache: true
    force_apt_get: true
  vars:
    packages:
    - apt-transport-https
    - ca-certificates
    - curl
    - gnupg-agent
    - software-properties-common
    - aptitude
- name: Add Docker GPG key
  apt_key:
    url: https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu/gpg
    id: 9DC858229FC7DD38854AE2D88D81803C0EBFCD88
- name: Add Docker repository
  apt_repository:
    repo: deb [arch=amd64] https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu  stable
- name: Enable cgroup memory and swapaccount
  lineinfile:
    dest: /etc/default/grub
    regexp: GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX=
    line: GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX="cgroup_enable=memory swapaccount=1"
  register: docker_cgroup
  when: docker_enable_cgroup_memory_and_swapaccount
- name: Update grub
  command: update-grub2
  register: docker_kernel
  when: docker_cgroup is changed
- name: Reboot server if docker kernel is changed
  reboot: null
  when: docker_kernel is changed
when: ansible_distribution == "Ubuntu"
starcoder-response:
name: Setup Docker repository to install docker engine on Ubuntu

Answer: when: ansible_distribution == 'Ubuntu'
ansible.builtin.apt_repository:
  repo: deb [arch=amd64 signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/docker-archive-keyring.gpg]

  filename: docker
  state: present
  update_cache: true

  line: display_errors = On
- regexp: ^;?error_log
  line: error_log = /var/log/php-fpm/{{ php_version }}-fpm.log
- regexp: ^;?log_errors
  line: log_errors = On
- regexp: ^;?php_fpm_listen.mode
  line: php_fpm_listen.mode = 755
- regexp: ^;?php_fpm_listen.owner

block:
- name: Create backup directory
  file:
    path: /home/{{ backup_user }}/backups
    state: directory
    owner: '{{ ansible_env.SUDO_USER | default(ansible_env.USER, true) | default(ansible_user_id,

    group: '{{ ansible_env.SUDO_USER | default(ansible_env.USER, true) | default(ansible_user_id,

    name: Bakcup Mongo Daily Backup
    minute: '3'
    hour: '3'
    job: /home/{{ backup_user }}/backups/backup.sh
    user: '{{ ansible_env.SUDO_USER | default(ansible_env.USER, true) | default(ansible_user_id,
      true) }}'
- name: Set cron job to run weekly
  cron:
    name: Bakcup Mongo Daily Backup
    minute: '30'
    hour: '3'
    job: /home/{{ backup_user }}/backups/backup.sh
    user: '{{ ansible_env.SUDO_USER | default(ansible_env.USER, true) | default(ansible_user_id,
      true) }}'

input: name: Change wall config to send notifications via proxmox-mail-forward
output:
ansible.builtin.lineinfile:
  path: /etc/apcupsd/apccontrol
  regexp: ^WALL=
  line: WALL="/usr/bin/proxmox-mail-forward"
notify: Restart apcupsd service

name: Change wall config to send notifications via proxmox-mail-forward

Answer: when: pve_wall_notify_proxmox_email!= ""
block:
- name: Get current wallpaper (pve-img)
  command: pve-img info /home//.pve-img
  register: wallpaper_current
  changed_when: false
- name: Set wallpaper using pve-img
  command: pve-img set-wallpaper /home//.pve-img
  register: wallpaper_updated
  changed_when: wallpaper_updated.stdout.find("Wallpaper updated")!= -
- name: Send mail when wallpaper changes using proxmox-mail-forward
  command: pve-mail-forward -f  -n "PVE  Wallpaper update" --subject "PVE  Wallpaper
    update" --body "Hello,\nPVE  Wallpaper update."
  when: wallpaper_updated.stdout.find("Wallpaper updated")!= - and pve_wall_notify_proxmox_email
  register: proxmox_mail_forward
when: (pve_wall_notify_proxmox_email!= "" and pve_system_shell == "bash")

input: name: SCORED | 17.6.4 | PATCH | (L1) Ensure 'Audit Removable Storage' is set to 'Success
output:
and Failure'
block:
- name: SCORED | 17.6.4 | AUDIT | (L1) Ensure 'Audit Removable Storage' is set to
    'Success and Failure' | Get current settings
  win_shell: AuditPol /get /subcategory:"Removable Storage" -r | ConvertFrom-Csv |
    Select-Object -expand "Inclusion Setting"
  changed_when: false
  failed_when: false
  register: rule_17_6_4_audit
- name: SCORED | 17.6.4 | PATCH | (L1) Ensure 'Audit Removable Storage' is set to
    'Success and Failure' | Set success
  win_shell: AuditPol /set /subcategory:"Removable Storage" /success:enable
  changed_when: '''Success'' not in rule_17_6_4_audit.stdout'
  when: '''Success'' not in rule_17_6_4_audit.stdout'
- name: SCORED | 17.6.4 | PATCH | (L1) Ensure 'Audit Removable Storage' is set to
    'Success and Failure' | Set failure
  win_shell: AuditPol /set /subcategory:"Removable Storage" /failure:enable
  changed_when: '''failure'' not in rule_17_6_4_audit.stdout'
  when: '''Failure'' not in rule_17_6_4_audit.stdout'
when:
- rule_17_6_4
tags:
- level1-domaincontroller
- level1-memberserver
- rule_17.6.4
- patch
starcoder-response:
name: SCORED | 17.6.4 | PATCH | (L1) Ensure 'Audit Removable Storage' is set to 'Success
  and Failure'
win_shell: AuditPol /set /subcategory:"Removable Storage" /success:enable
changed_when: '''Success'' not in rule_17_6_4_audit.stdout'
when:
- rule_17_6_4
- rule_17_6_4_audit is defined
- '''Success'' not in rule_17_6_4_audit.stdout'
tags:
- level1
- level2
- rule_17.6.4
- patch

output:
block:
- name: Update OS packages to latest
  package:
    name: '*'
    state: latest
- name: Install dependencies
  package:
    name: ''
    state: latest
  loop: glibc.i686libstdc++.i686
- name: Create steam system user
  user:
    name: steam
    comment: SteamCMD system user
    create_home: true
    shell: /bin/false
    system: true
- name: Create the SteamCMD directory
  file:
    path: /var/lib/steam
    state: directory
    mode: 480
    owner: steam
    group: steam
- name: Download SteamCMD installer
  unarchive:
    src: https://steamcdn-a.akamaihd.net/client/installer/steamcmd_linux.tar.gz
    dest: /var/lib/steam
    remote_src: true
    owner: steam
    group: steam
- name: Set permissions for SteamCMD directory
  file:
    path: /var/lib/steam
    owner: steam
    group: steam
    recurse: true
- name: Run the installer script
  shell: su - steam -s /bin/bash -c '/var/lib/steam/steamcmd.sh +quit'
- name: Set permissions on SteamCMD script
  file:
